==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/dʌm/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌm|-ʌm]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|'''[[dumber]]'''|'''[[dumbest]]'''}}

# Unable to [[speak]]; lacking power of speech.
#:''His younger brother had been born '''dumb''', and communicated with a self-taught kind of sign language.''
# {{cattag|informal|pejorative}} Describing something, especially a person, extremely [[stupid]].
#:''You big '''dumb''' oaf!  You can't fix an engine by hitting it with a hammer!''
# {{informal}} Describing something [[unintellectual]].
#:''Harry had a '''dumb''', brainless job moving boxes from one conveyor belt to another.''
# {{figurative}} [[pointless|Pointless]], or serving to create more problems than it solves.
#:''This is so '''dumb'''! We're just driving in circles; we should have asked for directions an hour ago.''

====Synonyms====
*(''unable to speak''): [[dumbstruck]], [[mute]], [[speechless]], [[wordless]]
*(''extremely stupid''): [[feeble-minded]], [[idiotic]], [[moronic]], [[stupid]]
*(''unintellectual''): [[banal]], [[brainless]], [[stupid]], [[vulgar]]
*(''pointless''): [[silly]], [[stupid]], [[insane]], [[ridiculous]]

